## What Is a Unitary Thrift?

A unitary thrift is a charteredÂ [holding company](https://www.investopedia.com/terms/h/holdingcompany.asp) that controls a single [thrift](https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/thrift.asp) entity. Historically unitary thrifts could engage in a broader range of activities than bank holding companies, however, they have come under increasing restrictions since the 2008 financial crisis.

